content:
This file defines the main dashboard page for the DocMed application. It provides an overview of the user's connected repositories, commit activity, and configured pairs.

**Purpose:**
To display key statistics and recent activity to users logged into the DocMed platform.

**Key Components & Logic:**

*   **`DashboardPage` (async function):**
    *   Fetches user authentication status using `@clerk/nextjs/server`.
    *   Asynchronously retrieves data for `repo-pairs`, `commit-log`, and `commit-count` from helper functions in the `lib` directory, conditional on the user being authenticated.
    *   Calculates `reposConnected` by filtering pairs that have both a `targetRepo` and `docRepo` defined.
    *   Renders a dashboard layout with a title, description, and three `StatCard` components for displaying aggregated metrics.
    *   Displays a recent activity section, listing recent commits if available, or a placeholder message if no commits have been handled.

*   **`StatCard` (React Component):**
    *   A reusable component for displaying statistics.
    *   **Props:**
        *   `icon`: A React component (e.g., from `lucide-react`) to be displayed as an icon.
        *   `label`: A string representing the label for the statistic (e.g., "Commits Handled").
        *   `value`: A number representing the value of the statistic.

**Usage Example:**
This component is the main entry point for the `/dashboard` route. It's rendered automatically by Next.js when a user navigates to this URL.

```tsx
// Inside app/dashboard/page.tsx

// ... other imports and logic

return (
  <div className="flex flex-col h-full p-8 gap-8">
    {/* ... header section ... */}

    {/* Stats Section */}
    <div className="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-3 gap-4">
      <StatCard
        icon={GitBranch}
        label="Repos Connected"
        value={reposConnected}
      />
      <StatCard
        icon={GitCommit}
        label="Commits Handled"
        value={commitCount}
      />
      <StatCard
        icon={Layers}
        label="Pairs Configured"
        value={pairs.length}
      />
    </div>

    {/* Recent Activity Section */}
    <div className="flex flex-col gap-3 flex-1 min-h-0">
      {/* ... commit log rendering ... */}
    </div>
  </div>
);
```
